Please find below instructions for automation installation in MAC machine:

1.Install Home brew in Mac machine-- Home brew is a (Pacakage manager) to install all software from your terminal by running  one command.
>Open terminal
>Run below command & install Home brew.
/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"

>After installtion run this command:brew cask install foo

>After installation, we need to install below software.
>>brew tap caskroom/versions
>>brew cask install intellij-idea-ce(Intellij -This is IDE for coding & running code.)
>> brew cask install java8 (Java)
>>brew cask install android-sdk (The Android SDK (software development kit) is a set of development tools used to develop applications for Android platform)
>>Install Node
brew install node
>>  Navigate to below link:
https://github.com/appium/appium-desktop/releases/tag/v1.11.0
>>Download(Appium 1.11.0.dmg) , after downloading install it.
>> Download Sourcetree for interacting with Framework repositories:
https://www.sourcetreeapp.com/
>>Please follow below URL which has all steps to set your java path including all syntax.
http://www.sajeconsultants.com/how-to-set-java_home-on-mac-os-x/

If your a new user in Git you need to generate a SSH key & save it into your git profile.
Below URL has all steps & syntax commands.
https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucketserver/creating-ssh-keys-776639788.html


2.Download the project to your system.
>>Open Source tree & navigate to project stash URl.
>>Navigate to Project & clone it(your local machine)
>>Once clone done, follow below steps to open & configure in Intellij

3.Configure sdk & java path in Appium.
>> Open Appium.
>> Navigate & open 'Edit Configurations'
>> Save below path for Android home
/Users/user_name/Library/Android/sdk- (the username is of your local machine).
>> Save below path for Java home
/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.8.0_201.jdk/Contents/Home

Note:Please note your path for above andriod sdk & java may vary as per your installation.
for getting path run below command.
Java:
/usr/libexec/java_home


4.Configure your Framwork in intellj
>>Open Intellij & import a Project from your cloned location.
>>Post> Go to Preference & install Maven Plugin(It will restart the Intellij post installation)
>>Open Intellij>> Go to Preference & install plugin cucumber for java & Gherkin.

Note: Unmark the substeps intellij plugin(don't install it.)
